        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 6:21AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 620 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Bryson City, or near Smoky Mountains-Fontana Area,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Smoky Mountains-Deep Creek, Smoky Mountains-Fontana Area, Whittier,
Luada, Fontana Lake, Almond, Bryson City, Alarka, Smoky
Mountains-Kuwohi, and Cherokee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
